<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,1528,2023]" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">
<bibRefCitation author="Cockerell, T. D. A. &amp; Casad, J. E." box="[151,455,1528,1554]" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" pagination="293 - 296" refId="ref36241" refString="Cockerell, T. D. A. &amp; Casad, J. E. (1894) New species of Mutillidae. Entomological News, 5, 293 - 296." type="journal article" year="1894">Cockerell &amp; Casad (1894)</bibRefCitation>
described two new species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[816,933,1528,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Mutillidae</taxonomicName>
based on material collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[1300,1432,1528,1554]" country="Mexico" name="Guanajuato" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">Guanajuato</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,275,1564,1590]" country="Mexico" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">Mexico by</collectingRegion>
Alfredo Dugès: 
<taxonomicName authority="Cockerell &amp; Casad" authorityName="Cockerell &amp; Casad" box="[472,1053,1563,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dugesii">
<emphasis box="[472,670,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">Sphaerophthalma</emphasis>
[sic] 
<emphasis box="[742,823,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">dugesii</emphasis>
Cockerell &amp; Casad
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cockerell &amp; Casad. Shortly" authorityName="Cockerell &amp; Casad. Shortly" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Ephuta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacantha">
<emphasis box="[1116,1284,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">S. megacantha</emphasis>
Cockerell &amp; Casad. Shortly
</taxonomicName>
after, two additional species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cockerell" authorityName="Cockerell" box="[656,933,1600,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prunotincta">
<emphasis box="[656,816,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">S. prunotincta</emphasis>
Cockerell
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cockerell &amp; Casad" authorityName="Cockerell &amp; Casad" box="[989,1369,1600,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufosuffusa">
<emphasis box="[989,1144,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">S. rufosuffusa</emphasis>
Cockerell &amp; Casad
</taxonomicName>
, were also described from material collected by Dugès in 
<collectingRegion box="[746,875,1636,1662]" country="Mexico" name="Guanajuato" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">Guanajuato</collectingRegion>
(Cockerell 1895; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cockerell, T. D. A. &amp; Casad, J. E." box="[1085,1372,1636,1663]" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" pagination="297 - 300" refId="ref36294" refString="Cockerell, T. D. A. &amp; Casad, J. E. (1895) Descriptions of new Hymenoptera. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 22, 297 - 300." type="journal article" year="1895">Cockerell &amp; Casad 1895</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[151,260,1672,1698]" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">holotypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[298,407,1672,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dugesii">
<emphasis box="[298,407,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">S. dugesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[421,587,1672,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Ephuta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacantha">
<emphasis box="[421,587,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">S. megacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[601,760,1672,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prunotincta">
<emphasis box="[601,760,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">S. prunotincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[822,976,1672,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufosuffusa">
<emphasis box="[822,976,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">S. rufosuffusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been considered lost for some time (
<bibRefCitation author="Mickel, C. E." box="[159,306,1708,1734]" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" pagination="1 - 351" refId="ref37820" refString="Mickel, C. E. (1928) Biological and taxonomic investigations on the mutillid wasps. United States National Museum, Bulletin 143, 1 - 351, pls. 1 - 5. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 7835957  page / 5 / mode / 1 up https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.143.1" type="journal article" year="1928">Mickel 1928</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mickel, C. E." box="[317,376,1708,1734]" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" pagination="163 - 171" refId="ref38028" refString="Mickel, C. E. (1964) Synonymical notes on Neotropical Mutillidae (Hymenoptera). Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London, Series B, Taxonomy, 33, 163 - 171. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1964. tb 01635. x" type="journal article" year="1964">1964</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Suarez, F. J." box="[387,529,1708,1734]" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" pagination="471 - 482" refId="ref39506" refString="Suarez, F. J. (1966 [&quot; 1965 &quot;]) Datos sobre Mutilidos neotropicales. VI. Dos nuevos generos de Pseudomethocini de Mejico y Brasil (Hymenoptera). Eos, Revista Espanola de Entomologia, Madrid, 41 (2 - 3), 471 - 482. http: // hdl. handle. net / 10261 / 162095" type="journal article" year="1966">Suárez 1966</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Manley, D. G. &amp; Pitts, J. P." box="[541,780,1708,1734]" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref37618" refString="Manley, D. G. &amp; Pitts, J. P. (2007) Tropical and subtropical velvet ants of the genus Dasymutilla Ashmead (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae) with descriptions of 45 new species. Zootaxa, 1487 (1), 1 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1487.1.1" type="journal article" year="2007">Manley &amp; Pitts 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Despite not having located and examined the 
<typeStatus box="[1308,1406,1708,1734]" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Mickel (1964)" authorityName=", Mickel" authorityYear="1964" box="[151,491,1744,1771]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Ephuta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacantha">
<emphasis box="[151,316,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">S. megacantha</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mickel, C. E." box="[330,491,1744,1771]" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" pagination="163 - 171" refId="ref38028" refString="Mickel, C. E. (1964) Synonymical notes on Neotropical Mutillidae (Hymenoptera). Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London, Series B, Taxonomy, 33, 163 - 171. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1964. tb 01635. x" type="journal article" year="1964">Mickel (1964)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
synonymized this species under 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gerstaecker)" baseAuthorityName="Gerstaecker" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[860,1321,1744,1771]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Pseudomethoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cardinalis">
<emphasis box="[860,1158,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">Pseudomethoca cardinalis</emphasis>
(Gerstaecker)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,1528,2023]" lastBlockId="49.[151,1437,151,573]" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="200" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">
We sought to locate these four lost 
<typeStatus box="[599,708,1780,1806]" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">holotypes</typeStatus>
with the hunch that Cockerell and Casad may have returned the material to Dugès in 
<collectingRegion box="[395,527,1816,1842]" country="Mexico" name="Guanajuato" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">Guanajuato</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[540,629,1816,1842]" name="Mexico" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. Mr. Néstor Quezadas Tapia at the Museo de Historia Natural Alfredo Dugès (
<collectionCode box="[236,345,1852,1878]" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">MADUG</collectionCode>
) kindly searched for these four type specimens and provided photographs to confirm their identity. The type of 
<taxonomicName box="[291,446,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufosuffusa">
<emphasis box="[291,446,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">S. rufosuffusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was discovered (label: “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1871" box="[728,912,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[728,912,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">Sphaeropthalma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<emphasis box="[936,1070,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">
<taxonomicName box="[936,1065,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufosuffusa">rufosuffusa</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
/ 
<emphasis box="[1094,1154,1889,1914]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">Type.</emphasis>
”), as well as a specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[182,292,1924,1950]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dugesii">
<emphasis box="[182,292,1924,1950]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">S. dugesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that is not labeled as a type but could potentially be it (label: “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1009,1207,1924,1950]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1009,1207,1924,1950]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">Sphaerophthalma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<emphasis box="[1231,1372,1924,1950]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">Dugesi, Ckll</emphasis>
<specimenCount box="[1379,1399,1924,1950]" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
.”). A specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[328,489,1960,1986]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prunotincta">
<emphasis box="[328,489,1960,1986]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="199">S. prunotincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was also found but it lacks labels; this could be the type based on its match with Cockerell’s original description, the apparent age of the specimen, and the appearance of the pin. It is worth noting that 
<bibRefCitation author="Andre, E." box="[199,351,151,177]" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" pagination="1 - 79" refId="ref35023" refString="Andre, E. (1898) Etude sur les Mutillides du Museum de Paris. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 67, 1 - 79." type="journal article" year="1898">André (1898)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that he examined the type of 
<taxonomicName box="[810,970,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prunotincta">
<emphasis box="[810,970,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">S. prunotincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
through A. Dugès. No specimens labeled as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Mickel" authorityYear="1964" box="[182,347,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Ephuta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacantha">
<emphasis box="[182,347,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">S. megacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were located at MADUG.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">
Based on the original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Mickel" authorityYear="1964" box="[624,792,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Ephuta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacantha">
<emphasis box="[624,792,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">S. megacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cockerell, T. D. A. &amp; Casad, J. E." box="[840,1146,223,249]" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" pagination="293 - 296" refId="ref36241" refString="Cockerell, T. D. A. &amp; Casad, J. E. (1894) New species of Mutillidae. Entomological News, 5, 293 - 296." type="journal article" year="1894">Cockerell &amp; Casad (1894)</bibRefCitation>
, it is likely a member of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Suarez" authorityYear="1966" box="[151,259,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Invreiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,259,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">Invreiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; however, there is not enough information to determine with certainty its species-level identity. Due to the unexpected diversity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Suarez" authorityYear="1966" box="[463,571,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Invreiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[463,571,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">Invreiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
discovered during the course of this study, we here treat 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Mickel" authorityYear="1964" box="[1211,1372,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Ephuta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacantha">
<emphasis box="[1211,1372,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">I. megacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">stat. resurr.</emphasis>
, as a 
<emphasis box="[296,462,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">nomen dubium</emphasis>
with the hope that type material will eventually surface. It is possible that 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Mickel" authorityYear="1964" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Ephuta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">I. megacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is indeed a synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gerstaecker" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[467,605,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Pseudomethoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cardinalis">
<emphasis box="[467,605,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">I. cardinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as A. Dugès’ brother, Eugenio Dugès, collected a female of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gerstaecker" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1299,1437,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Pseudomethoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cardinalis">
<emphasis box="[1299,1437,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">I. cardinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[180,313,403,429]" country="Mexico" name="Guanajuato" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">Guanajuato</collectingRegion>
; this specimen is housed at RBINS. As for the other three types, 
<bibRefCitation author="Manley, D. G. &amp; Pitts, J. P." box="[1037,1290,403,429]" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref37618" refString="Manley, D. G. &amp; Pitts, J. P. (2007) Tropical and subtropical velvet ants of the genus Dasymutilla Ashmead (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae) with descriptions of 45 new species. Zootaxa, 1487 (1), 1 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1487.1.1" type="journal article" year="2007">Manley &amp; Pitts (2007)</bibRefCitation>
designated a 
<typeStatus box="[151,240,439,465]" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">neotype</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName box="[285,393,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dugesii">
<emphasis box="[285,393,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">S. dugesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species that is now considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Cockerell, 1894) (Pilgrim et al. 2008)" authorityName="Pilgrim et al." authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Cockerell" baseAuthorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Dasymutilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foxi">
<emphasis box="[923,1108,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">Dasymutilla foxi</emphasis>
(Cockerell, 1894) (
<bibRefCitation author="Pilgrim, E. M. &amp; Williams, K. A. &amp; Pitts, J. P." pageId="49" pageNumber="200" pagination="57 - 68" refId="ref38691" refString="Pilgrim, E. M., Williams, K. A. &amp; Pitts, J. P. (2008) Sex association and synonymy in southwestern U. S. species of Dasymutilla (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae). The Pan-Pacific Entomologist, 84 (1), 57 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.3956 / 2007 - 13.1" type="journal article" year="2008">
Pilgrim 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The species 
<taxonomicName box="[405,564,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prunotincta">
<emphasis box="[405,564,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">S. prunotincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was synonymized under 
<taxonomicName authority="Saussure, 1867" authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1867" box="[849,1337,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sicheliana" subGenus="Ephuta">
<emphasis box="[849,931,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">Mutilla</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[948,1029,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">Ephuta</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1045,1160,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">sicheliana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Saussure, H. de" box="[1167,1337,475,501]" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" pagination="351 - 364" refId="ref39122" refString="Saussure, H. de (1867) Mutillarum novarum species aliquot. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 7, 351 - 364, pl. VIII." type="journal article" year="1867">Saussure, 1867</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Dasymutilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sicheliana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">Dasymutilla sicheliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Andre, E." box="[403,559,511,537]" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" pagination="1 - 79" refId="ref35023" refString="Andre, E. (1898) Etude sur les Mutillides du Museum de Paris. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 67, 1 - 79." type="journal article" year="1898">André (1898)</bibRefCitation>
. Lastly, the species 
<taxonomicName box="[781,936,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaerophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufosuffusa">
<emphasis box="[781,936,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">S. rufosuffusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is likely a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Blake, 1871)" baseAuthorityName="Blake" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Dasymutilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosa">
<emphasis box="[1200,1436,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="200">Dasymutilla formosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Blake, C. A." box="[159,300,547,573]" pageId="49" pageNumber="200" pagination="217 - 265" refId="ref35467" refString="Blake, C. A. (1871) Synopsis of the Mutillidae of North America. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 3, 217 - 265 + 358." type="journal article" year="1871">Blake, 1871</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
